I"^<p>Building a landing page using Bootstrap4. Starting with template from the <a href="https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.4/getting-started/introduction/">Bootstrap</a> website. This is mostly a refresher, but it’s been a long time since I’ve touched any of this. Most customization options are documented on the Bootstrap site for convenience.</p>

<hr />

<p><strong>Creating a Navigation Bar</strong></p>

<p>Define the <code class="highlighter-rouge">nav class</code>, specify what your buttons will look like; create <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;div&gt;</code> and <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;ul&gt;</code> classes within each other to hold your list of links. Each link within the navbar is its own item.</p>

<hr />

<p><strong>The Jumbotron</strong></p>

<p>Section named <code class="highlighter-rouge">top</code> for nav purposes. Contains page title, minor descriptive flavor text, important links (like where to get a product).</p>

<hr />

<p><strong>Sections</strong></p>

<p>Each block of the page is contained within a <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;section&gt;</code>. Each section gets a class for navigation purposes.</p>

